The paper discusses a technique called pansharpening, which is used to increase the spatial resolution of multispectral data while preserving its spectral information. This technique is commonly used in remote sensing and image processing, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses an optimization problem and a nonlocal regularization term, which are related to mathematical modeling and optimization (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper compares the proposed method with several classical and state-of-the-art pansharpening techniques, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
